 Mike Tammadge, Middelburg Mall manager, said that they made the decision to evacuate the building because of the presence of smoke in the vicinity of Checkers.
Initial reports were that there was a fire in the roof of the building. The Fire Department was called to the scene to assess the situation. Also read: Shoppers evacuated from Middelburg Mall Mr Tammadge said that it was established that transformers that overheated, causing plastic wiring to catch fire, was the cause of the black smoke that was visible.
After they received the “all clear” from the Fire Brigade, the mall was declared safe and reopened to customers. • In spite of suspicions by residents, the power cut in Aerorand was not related to the electrical problem at the mall.      Four killed after minibus and truck collide on N11 near Doornkop Elderly lady escapes with her life Parkrun fever breaks out Military troop imposter arrested • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za     